affic PCAP generator\n37:   - Function: `create_basic_http_pcap(output_path)`\n38:   - Packets: HTTP GET request + HTTP response\n39:   - Output: `test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n40:   - Verify: `python sample_pcap.py` generates file > 0 bytes\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.3** Implement DNS queries PCAP generator\n43:   - Function: `create_dns_queries_pcap(output_path)`\n44:   - Packets: DNS queries (example.com, google.com) + responses\n45:   - Output: `test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n46:   - Verify: Generated PCAP contains DNS layers\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.4** Test sample generation\n49:   - Command: `cd sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer && python sample_pcap.py`\n50:   - Verify: Both `basic_http.pcap` and `dns_queries.pcap` exist\n51:   - Verify: Files can be read by wireshark/tcpdump\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Phase 3: PCAP Analyzer Core Implementation\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T3.1** Create pcap_analyzer.py main script\n58:   - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n59:   - Imports: os, sys, json, logging, pathlib, typing, agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\n60:   - Verify: File exists with correct structure\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement PcapAnalyzer class initialization\n63:   - Class: `PcapAnalyzer`\n64:   - Method: `__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url, auth_token, verbose)`\n65:   - Initialize: `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"pcap-analyzer\")`\n66:   - Set paths: `remote_pcap_dir`, `remote_results_dir`, `remote_analyzer_script`\n67:   - Verify: Class can be instantiated\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement setup_environment method\n70:   - Method: `setup_environment()`\n71:   - Commands: `mkdir -p` for directories, `pip install scapy --quiet`\n72:   - Verify: Sandbox directories created and scapy installed\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement upload_pcap method\n75:   - Method: `upload_pcap(local_path) -> str`\n76:   - Validation: Check file exists\n77:   - Upload: `client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n78:   - Verify: `client.list_files()` shows uploaded file\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement create_analyzer_script method\n81:   - Method: `create_analyzer_script()`\n82:   - Script content: `analyze_pcap(pcap_path)` function\n83:   - Features: Protocol detection (TCP/UDP/OTHER), IP extraction, port extraction, DNS query extraction\n84:   - Write: `client.write_file(script_content, remote_analyzer_script)`\n85:   - Verify: Script exists in sandbox\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement analyze_pcap method\n88:   - Method: `analyze_pcap(remote_pcap_path) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n89:   - Execute: `client.run_code()` with analyzer script\n90:   - Download: `client.download_file(output_path, local_path)`\n91:   - Return: Parsed JSON results\n92:   - Error handling: CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError\n93:   - Verify: Returns correct analysis results\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.7** Implement close method\n96:   - Method: `close()`\n97:   - Action: `client.stop()`\n98:   - Verify: Session properly cleaned up\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 4: CLI & Entry Point\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T4.1** Implement command-line argument parsing\n105:   - Function: `main()`\n106:   - Arguments: `pcap_file` (positional), `--router-url`, `--workload-manager-url`, `--auth-token`, `-v/--verbose`, `--generate-samples`\n107:   - Epilog: Usage examples\n108:   - Verify: `python pcap_analyzer.py --help` shows all arguments\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.2** Implement main execution flow\n111:   - Flow: Check generate-samples → Validate file → Initialize analyzer → Setup → Create script → Upload → Analyze → Print results\n112:   - Output: JSON formatted results\n113:   - Verify: Complete flow executes without errors\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.3** Implement error handling\n116:   - Exceptions: FileNotFoundError, CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError, generic Exception\n117:   - Finally block: Call `analyzer.close()`\n118:   - Verify: Errors are caught and logged appropriately\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Phase 5: Testing & Validation\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T5.1** Test sample generation\n125:   - Command: `python sample_pcap.py`\n126:   - Verify: Two PCAP files created in test_pcaps/\n127:   - Verify: Files are valid PCAP format\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T5.2** Test basic HTTP PCAP analysis\n130:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n131:   - Verify: Output contains `total_packets: 2`\n132:   - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {TCP: 2}`\n133:   - Verify: Output contains IP addresses\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.3** Test DNS PCAP analysis\n136:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n137:   - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {UDP: ...}`\n138:   - Verify: Output contains `dns_queries: [\"example.com\", \"google.com\"]`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T5.4** Test error handling - missing file\n141:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py nonexistent.pcap`\n142:   - Verify: FileNotFoundError is raised and logged\n143: \n144: - [ ] **T5.5** Test verbose mode\n145:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap -v`\n146:   - Verify: DEBUG level logs are displayed\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T5.6** Test generate-samples flag\n149:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py --generate-samples`\n150:   - Verify: Samples generated and analyzed in one run\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T5.7** Test missing ROUTER_URL\n153:   - Command: Unset ROUTER_URL and run analyzer\n154:   - Verify: Appropriate error message displayed\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Phase 6: Acceptance Verification\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T6.1** Verify all spec requirements (delta-spec-ar-037.md)\n161:   - [ ] PCAP file parsing with scapy\n162:   - [ ] Protocol statistics (TCP/UDP/OTHER)\n163:   - [ ] IP address statistics (source/destination)\n164:   - [ ] Port statistics (TCP/UDP)\n165:   - [ ] DNS query extraction\n166:   - [ ] AgentCube SDK integration (CodeInterpreterClient)\n167:   - [ ] CLI argument parsing\n168:   - [ ] JSON output format\n169:   - [ ] Error handling\n170:   - [ ] requirements.txt exists\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T6.2** Code quality check\n173:   - Verify: PEP 8 compliance (no linting errors)\n174:   - Verify: Type annotations present\n175:   - Verify: Logging is informative\n176:   - Verify: No hardcoded secrets\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T6.3** Documentation completeness\n179:   - Verify: README has Features, Prerequisites, Installation, Usage sections\n180:   - Verify: README has Example Output section\n181:   - Verify: README has Troubleshooting section\n182:   - Verify: README has Advanced Usage section\n183: \n184: - [ ] **T6.4** Final integration test\n185:   - Command: Full workflow from clean directory\n186:   - Steps: Install deps → Generate samples → Run analysis → Verify output\n187:   - Verify: End-to-end workflow completes successfully\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## Dependencies\n192: \n193: **Required:**\n194: - Python 3.10+\n195: - AgentCube Python SDK\n196: - Router service (ROUTER_URL env var)\n197: - scapy>=2.5.0\n198: \n199: **Blocked By:**\n200: - AR-028/AR-029 (SDK HTTP client implementation)\n201: \n202: **References:**\n203: - `delta-spec-ar-037.md` - Delta Specification\n204: - `changes/AR-037/proposal.md` - Implementation Proposal\n205: - `sdk-python/design.md` - SDK Design\n206: - `sdk-python/spec.md` - SDK Specification\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用 Tasks\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** Not started\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Project Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create example directory structure\n  - Directory: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/`\n  - Subdirectory: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/test_pcaps/`\n  - Verify: `ls -la sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/` shows directories\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt`\n  - Content: `scapy>=2.5.0`\n  - Verify: `cat requirements.txt` shows scapy dependency","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775891416522,"end":1775891416536}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891416542,"sessionID":"ses_2849fd21bffeUKa4X2cYGkL1x4","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6080b7001gwKkVBMBnENutu","messageID":"msg_d7b606b82001NclnBCzTOqbuWG","sessionID":"ses_2849fd21bffeUKa4X2cYGkL1x4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_03f262f56b0c42ec97928700","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/run_e2e.sh"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/run_e2e.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/bin/bash\n2: # E2E test runner for AgentCube\n3: # This script sets up a Kind cluster, installs dependencies, and runs E2E tests\n4: \n5: set -e\n6: \n7: # Configuration\n8: export E2E_CLUSTER_NAME=${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME:-agentcube-e2e}\n9: export E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=${E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER:-true}\n10: export E2E_SKIP_SETUP=${E2E_SKIP_SETUP:-false}\n11: export AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-agentcube}\n12: export AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION=${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION:-v0.1.1}\n13: export WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT=${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT:-8080}\n14: export ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT=${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT:-8081}\n15: export REDIS_IMAGE=${REDIS_IMAGE:-redis:7-alpine}\n16: export E2E_VENV_DIR=${E2E_VENV_DIR:-/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv}\n17: export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${ARTIFACTS_PATH:-${PWD}/e2e-logs}\n18: \n19: # Colors for output\n20: RED='\\033[0;31m'\n21: GREEN='\\033[0;32m'\n22: YELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\n23: NC='\\033[0m' # No Color\n24: \n25: log_info() {\n26:     echo -e \"${GREEN}[INFO]${NC} $1\"\n27: }\n28: \n29: log_warn() {\n30:     echo -e \"${YELLOW}[WARN]${NC} $1\"\n31: }\n32: \n33: log_error() {\n34:     echo -e \"${RED}[ERROR]${NC} $1\"\n35: }\n36: \n37: # Collect component logs on failure\n38: collect_component_logs() {\n39:     log_info \"Collecting component logs...\"\n40:     mkdir -p \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH\"\n41:     \n42:     # Collect workload manager logs\n43:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" logs -l app=workloadmanager > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/workloadmanager.log\" 2>/dev/null || true\n44:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" describe pod -l app=workloadmanager > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/workloadmanager-describe.txt\" 2>/dev/null || true\n45:     \n46:     # Collect router logs\n47:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" logs -l app=agentcube-router > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/router.log\" 2>/dev/null || true\n48:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" describe pod -l app=agentcube-router > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/router-describe.txt\" 2>/dev/null || true\n49:     \n50:     # Collect sandbox pod logs\n51:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" logs -l app=agent-sandbox-controller > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/sandbox.log\" 2>/dev/null || true\n52:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" describe pod -l app=agent-sandbox-controller > \"$ARTIFACTS_PATH/sandbox-describe.txt\" 2>/dev/null || true\n53:     \n54:     log_info \"Logs collected in $ARTIFACTS_PATH\"\n55: }\n56: \n57: # Run setup\n58: run_setup() {\n59:     log_info \"Setting up E2E environment...\"\n60:     \n61:     # Check if cluster exists\n62:     if kind get clusters 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"^${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}$\"; then\n63:         if [ \"$E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER\" = \"true\" ]; then\n64:             log_info \"Deleting existing cluster...\"\n65:             kind delete cluster --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n66:         fi\n67:     fi\n68:     \n69:     # Create Kind cluster\n70:     log_info \"Creating Kind cluster...\"\n71:     kind create cluster --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n72:     \n73:     # Download and apply agent-sandbox manifests\n74:     log_info \"Installing agent-sandbox ${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}...\"\n75:     wget -q \"https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml\" -O /tmp/manifest.yaml\n76:     wget -q \"https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml\" -O /tmp/extensions.yaml\n77:     kubectl apply --validate=false -f /tmp/manifest.yaml\n78:     kubectl apply --validate=false -f /tmp/extensions.yaml\n79:     \n80:     # Pull required images\n81:     log_info \"Pulling required images...\"\n82:     docker pull \"registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}\"\n83:     docker pull python:3.9-slim\n84:     docker pull \"$REDIS_IMAGE\"\n85:     \n86:     # Build local images\n87:     log_info \"Building local images...\"\n88:     make docker-build\n89:     make docker-build-router\n90:     make docker-build-picod\n91:     \n92:     # Load images to Kind\n93:     log_info \"Loading images to Kind cluster...\"\n94:     kind load docker-image \"workloadmanager:latest\" --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n95:     kind load docker-image \"agentcube-router:latest\" --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n96:     kind load docker-image \"picod:latest\" --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n97:     kind load docker-image \"$REDIS_IMAGE\" --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n98:     kind load docker-image \"registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}\" --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n99:     \n100:     # Create namespace\n101:     kubectl create namespace \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n102:     \n103:     # Install Redis\n104:     log_info \"Installing Redis...\"\n105:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" run redis --image=\"$REDIS_IMAGE\" --port=6379 --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n106:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" expose pod redis --port=6379 --target-port=6379 --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n107:     \n108:     # Install AgentCube via Helm\n109:     log_info \"Installing AgentCube chart...\"\n110:     helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n111:         --namespace \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" \\\n112:         --create-namespace \\\n113:         --set redis.host=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local\" \\\n114:         --set redis.port=6379 \\\n115:         --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n116:         --set workloadmanager.image.repository=workloadmanager \\\n117:         --set workloadmanager.image.tag=latest \\\n118:         --set router.image.repository=agentcube-router \\\n119:         --set router.image.tag=latest \\\n120:         --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n121:         --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n122:         --set-json='workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n123:         --set-json='router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n124:         --wait\n125:     \n126:     # Apply fixtures\n127:     log_info \"Applying E2E fixtures...\"\n128:     kubectl apply -f test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml\n129:     kubectl apply -f test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n130:     \n131:     # Generate short TTL agent\n132:     sed 's/sessionTimeout: \"5m\"/sessionTimeout: \"30s\"/' test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml | \\\n133:         sed 's/name: echo-agent/name: echo-agent-short-ttl/' | \\\n134:         kubectl apply -f -\n135:     \n136:     # Wait for deployments\n137:     log_info \"Waiting for deployments to be ready...\"\n138:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" rollout status deployment/workloadmanager --timeout=120s\n139:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" rollout status deployment/agentcube-router --timeout=120s\n140:     \n141:     # Set up port forwarding\n142:     log_info \"Setting up port forwarding...\"\n143:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" port-forward svc/workloadmanager ${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}:8080 &\n144:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" port-forward svc/agentcube-router ${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}:8080 &\n145:     sleep 3\n146:     \n147:     # Health checks\n148:     log_info \"Running health checks...\"\n149:     curl -s \"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health\" || exit 1\n150:     curl -s \"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live\" || exit 1\n151:     \n152:     # Create service account and token for tests\n153:     log_info \"Creating test service account...\"\n154:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" create sa e2e-test --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n155:     kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" create clusterrolebinding e2e-test-binding \\\n156:         --clusterrole=workloadmanager \\\n157:         --serviceaccount=\"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\":e2e-test \\\n158:         --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n159:     export API_TOKEN=$(kubectl -n \"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\" create token e2e-test --duration=24h)\n160:     \n161:     # Set up Python virtual environment\n162:     log_info \"Setting up Python virtual environment...\"\n163:     if [ ! -d \"$E2E_VENV_DIR\" ]; then\n164:         python3 -m venv \"$E2E_VENV_DIR\"\n165:         \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/pip\" install --upgrade pip\n166:         \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/pip\" install -e ./sdk-python\n167:     fi\n168:     \n169:     # Verify agentcube import\n170:     \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" -c \"import agentcube\" || exit 1\n171:     \n172:     log_info \"E2E environment setup complete!\"\n173: }\n174: \n175: # Run E2E tests\n176: run_tests() {\n177:     log_info \"Running E2E tests...\"\n178:     \n179:     # Run Go tests\n180:     log_info \"Running Go E2E tests...\"\n181:     WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n182:     ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n183:     API_TOKEN=\"$API_TOKEN\" \\\n184:     go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n185:     \n186:     # Run Python tests\n187:     log_info \"Running Python E2E tests...\"\n188:     cd test/e2e\n189:     WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n190:     ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n191:     API_TOKEN=\"$API_TOKE